name: Spun gold
description: An atomic force microscope image that I took of the plant cell wall, from an onion sample, showing individual cellulose microfibrils. Each of these fibers is approximately 3.5 nanometers in width, which is about 25,000 times smaller than a human hair. This is the most powerful type of microscope in the world, and among the highest resolution images ever taken of a biological sample like this.
